Inheritance allows a class (called child or subclass) to acquire properties and behaviors (methods) 
from another class (called parent or superclass).
This promotes:
This promotes:
Code reusability
Method overriding (polymorphism)
Cleaner and more manageable code structure
"Is-a" relationship modeling



