super() is a built-in function used to call methods or constructors from a parent (base) class. 
It is most commonly used in inheritance, especially with method overriding.

Why Use super()?
To call parent class method from child class

To avoid duplicating code

To support multiple inheritance cleanly

To extend functionality rather than replace




